---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---

<Layout title="Free Scrabble Solver Guide — Tips, Filters & Strategy" description="Learn how to use our free Scrabble word finder. Master tile entry, filters, rack leave analysis, bingo hunting, and strategy tips. No sign-up required." keywords="scrabble word finder guide, scrabble strategy tips, scrabble rack leave, scrabble opening moves, scrabble bingo words, free word finder tutorial, scrabble tile probability">
<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 pt-4 pb-6">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-2">User Guide</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-8">Everything you need to know to get the most out of ScrabbleWordsFinder.com.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-3 border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-3">Entering Your Tiles</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">You have two ways to input your rack tiles, and they stay perfectly in sync:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span><strong class="text-white">Word Solver (text box):</strong> Type up to 15 letters directly. Results appear as you type — no need to click anything. Press Enter or click <strong class="text-white">Solve</strong> as a fallback if auto-search doesn't fire.</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span><strong class="text-white">Tile Rack (7 boxes):</strong> Click individual tile slots to enter one letter per box. The cursor moves right automatically after each letter. Press Backspace to go left. Click <strong class="text-white">Find Words</strong> to search.</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-purple-400 mt-6 mb-3">🔄 Bidirectional Sync</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">The Word Solver and Tile Rack are linked — type in one, and the other updates instantly:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Type "SCRABBLE" in the Word Solver → the first 7 letters fill the Tile Rack boxes automatically</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Fill the Tile Rack boxes → the Word Solver text field updates to match</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>The Word Solver supports up to 15 letters (for longer searches), while the Tile Rack shows the first 7</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-purple-400 mt-6 mb-3">✖️ Clear Button</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">The purple ✖️ button between the Word Solver and the Solve button clears everything in one click:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Clears the Word Solver text</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Clears all 7 Tile Rack boxes</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Resets the results panel to "Enter at least 2 tiles"</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Use it to start a fresh search without refreshing the page</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-purple-400 mt-6 mb-3">🔘 Solve vs Find Words</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Both buttons trigger word search, but they work slightly differently:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span><strong class="text-white">Solve</strong> — uses the full Word Solver text (up to 15 letters). Finds all words up to your tile count length.</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span><strong class="text-white">Find Words</strong> — reads from the hidden tiles field. If you have more than 7 tiles (via the text solver), it searches the full set. With 7 or fewer, it caps at 7-letter words.</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Both are fallbacks — the solver normally searches automatically as you type (300ms debounce). Use the buttons if results don't appear.</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-3 border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-3">Using Blank Tiles (?)</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Blank tiles are wildcards that can represent any letter. Enter them as a question mark (<code class="bg-gray-800 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-blue-400">?</code>) in your rack.</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>You can use up to 2 blanks (matching a real Scrabble set)</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Words using blanks will show the blank letter in lowercase in results</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Blank tiles score 0 points, so the solver accounts for this in point totals</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-3 border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-3">Filters &amp; Options</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Narrow down results to find exactly the word you need:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span><strong class="text-white">Dictionary:</strong> Switch between SOWPODS (international, 74,000+ words) and TWL (North American tournament list)</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span><strong class="text-white">Sort by:</strong> Points (highest first), length, or alphabetical</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span><strong class="text-white">Minimum length:</strong> Only show words of a certain length or longer</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span><strong class="text-white">Contains:</strong> Only show words containing a specific letter or sequence</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span><strong class="text-white">Starts with:</strong> Filter words by their opening letters</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span><strong class="text-white">Ends with:</strong> Filter words by their ending letters</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>📖 For more on how dictionaries differ, read <a href="/blog/scrabble-dictionaries-languages-weird-words" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 underline underline-offset-2">Scrabble Dictionaries: Languages & Weird Words</a></span></li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-3 border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-3">Achievements &amp; Memory Workbench</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Track your progress and build your personal word bank:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Click any word in the results to save it to your 👑 Memory Workbench collection with an auto-fetched definition</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Memory Workbench persist in your browser and can be backed up to our server via your UUID</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Review, edit, or delete memory workbench from the Memory Workbench panel on the solver page</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-purple-400 mt-6 mb-3">🏅 Score-Based Achievements</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">When you click a word in the results, the Tile Scores panel shows your score and awards you an achievement level. There are 5 levels:</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
      <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
        <thead class="bg-gray-800">
          <tr>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left text-gray-300">Level</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left text-gray-300">Name</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left text-gray-300">Score</th>
            <th class="px-4 py-2 text-left text-gray-300">Icon</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
          <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-200">Rising Star</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">1–9 pts</td><td class="px-4 py-2">⭐</td></tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-900/50"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-200">Word Builder</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">10–19 pts</td><td class="px-4 py-2">👍</td></tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-200">Hot Streak</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">20–29 pts</td><td class="px-4 py-2">🔥</td></tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-900/50"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-200">Triple Threat</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">30–49 pts</td><td class="px-4 py-2">🏆</td></tr>
          <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-200">Scrabble Legend</td><td class="px-4 py-2 text-gray-400">50+ pts</td><td class="px-4 py-2">🌟</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">When you see your achievement, click <strong class="text-purple-300">Save</strong> to file it permanently. You can add an optional note before saving. All filed achievements are stored in your account and linked to your UUID.</p>

    <div class="rounded-lg border border-blue-800/40 bg-blue-900/10 p-4 mb-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium mb-2">💡 Memory Workbench — Your Personal Word Memory Tool</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-2">The Memory Workbench works like a set of flash cards. As you solve words and save them, each entry gets a definition — creating a personal vocabulary deck you can scroll through anytime to jog your memory.</p>
      <ul class="text-xs text-gray-400 space-y-1">
        <li>→ Use the ◀ ▶ arrows to flip through your saved words like memory cards</li>
        <li>→ Each card shows the word, its score, and meaning — perfect for recall practice</li>
        <li>→ Add personal notes to words (click ✏️ Edit) to create mnemonics or context</li>
        <li>→ Over time, your workbench becomes a curated study deck of words you discovered through play</li>
        <li>→ Many players report noticeably better spelling accuracy and word recall after regular use</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-3 border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-3">🎲 Tile Probability Tracker</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Track what's left in the bag and plan your moves with probability data.</p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-purple-400 mt-6 mb-3">Setting Up the Tile Bag</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Before starting a game, set your Bag and Played values to accurately track remaining tiles:</p>

    <!-- Live Tile Bag control (syncs with solver) -->
    <div class="rounded-xl border border-purple-800/50 bg-gray-900/50 p-4 mb-6">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-3">
        <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-white flex items-center gap-1.5"><span aria-hidden="true">🎲</span> Tile Bag</span>
        <button id="guide-reset-bag" class="px-2 py-1 rounded bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-xs font-medium text-gray-400 hover:text-rose-400 hover:border-rose-700 transition-colors">↺ Reset</button>
      </div>
      <div class="flex items-center gap-5 text-xs">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
          <span class="text-gray-400 font-medium">Bag:</span>
          <input id="guide-bag" type="number" min="0" max="100" value="100" class="w-[45px] text-center text-xs font-bold text-white bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 rounded px-1.5 py-1 focus:outline-none focus:border-blue-500" />
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
          <span class="text-gray-400 font-medium">Rack:</span>
          <span id="guide-rack" class="text-xs font-bold text-blue-400">0</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5">
          <span class="text-gray-400 font-medium">Played:</span>
          <input id="guide-played" type="number" min="0" max="100" value="0" class="w-[45px] text-center text-xs font-bold text-rose-400 bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 rounded px-1.5 py-1 focus:outline-none focus:border-blue-500" />
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mt-3 italic">↑ Values sync with the solver. Set them here or on the solver page — they persist in your browser.</p>
    </div>

    <script>
      const PROB_KEY = 'scbTileProb';
      const bagInput = document.getElementById('guide-bag') as HTMLInputElement | null;
      const playedInput = document.getElementById('guide-played') as HTMLInputElement | null;
      const rackDisplay = document.getElementById('guide-rack');
      const resetBtn = document.getElementById('guide-reset-bag');

      if (bagInput && playedInput) {
        // Load existing values from localStorage
        try {
          const saved = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem(PROB_KEY) || '{}');
          if (saved.inBag !== undefined) bagInput.value = String(saved.inBag);
          if (saved.played !== undefined) playedInput.value = String(saved.played);
        } catch {}

        // Save to localStorage on every value change
        function saveValues() {
          const inBag = parseInt(bagInput!.value) || 0;
          const played = parseInt(playedInput!.value) || 0;
          localStorage.setItem(PROB_KEY, JSON.stringify({ inBag, played }));
        }

        bagInput.addEventListener('input', saveValues);
        bagInput.addEventListener('change', saveValues);
        playedInput.addEventListener('input', saveValues);
        playedInput.addEventListener('change', saveValues);

        // Reset button — restores starting values
        if (resetBtn) {
          resetBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
            bagInput.value = '100';
            playedInput.value = '0';
            if (rackDisplay) rackDisplay.textContent = '0';
            localStorage.setItem(PROB_KEY, JSON.stringify({ inBag: 100, played: 0 }));
          });
        }
      }
    </script>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-4">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">1.</span><span><strong class="text-white">Bag</strong> — set to the number of tiles remaining in the physical bag (starts at 100 in a standard game, decreases as players draw)</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">2.</span><span><strong class="text-white">Played</strong> — set to the number of tiles already on the board (increases each turn as words are placed)</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">3.</span><span><strong class="text-white">Rack</strong> — auto-calculated from your current tile input (shows how many tiles you have on your rack)</span></li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">💡 These values are saved in your browser — they persist between sessions so you can resume tracking mid-game.</p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-purple-400 mt-6 mb-3">What the Tracker Shows</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-4">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>How many of each letter remain in the tile bag based on what you've played</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Click "Draw %" to see probability of drawing specific high-value tiles (Z, Q, X, J)</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Helps you decide whether to exchange tiles, play defensively, or go for a bingo</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-purple-400 mt-6 mb-3">Strategy Tips</h3>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>When the bag is low (&lt;10 tiles), you can deduce your opponent's rack by counting played letters</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>If high-value tiles (Q, Z) haven't appeared and the bag is shrinking, play defensively to avoid giving your opponent triple-word access</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Track S tiles — if all 4 are played, your opponent can't pluralise your words</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-3 border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-3">Rack Leave Analyzer</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Not just about the word you play — it's about what you keep. The rack leave analyzer evaluates what tiles remain on your rack after each possible play, helping you:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Avoid keeping clunky combinations (QU without a U, too many consonants)</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Maintain a balanced rack for future turns</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Maximize your scoring potential over multiple turns, not just this one</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-3 border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-3">Best Opening Moves</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">When you go first, the solver highlights optimal opening plays that:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Cover the center star (double word score)</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Balance points scored vs. rack leave quality</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Avoid opening up triple word squares for your opponent</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-3 border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-3">Backup &amp; Restore (User ID)</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Your data lives in your browser by default, but you can back it up:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span><strong class="text-white">Download User ID:</strong> Go to Settings and copy or download your anonymous UUID. This is the only key to your saved data.</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span><strong class="text-white">Relink on another device:</strong> Paste your UUID into the Restore field on Settings to pull your memory workbench and achievements onto a new browser.</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>No email or account needed — your UUID is your identity.</span></li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-3">⚙️ <a href="/settings" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 underline underline-offset-2">Go to Settings</a> to manage your backup, download your UID, or nuke localStorage.</p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-3 border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-3">Tips for Getting the Most Out of the Tool</h2>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-6">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">✓</span><span>Use the "Contains" filter when you see a hook opportunity on the board (e.g., add S to an existing word)</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">✓</span><span>Check rack leave before committing — a 30-point word with great leave beats a 35-point word with garbage leave</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">✓</span><span>Learn the 2-letter words — they're essential for parallel plays. Use min length = 2 and max length = 2 to study them</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">✓</span><span>Save words you didn't know — review them later to build your vocabulary</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">✓</span><span>Switch dictionaries if you play both casual (SOWPODS) and tournament (TWL) games</span></li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Gameplay Tactics & Strategies -->
    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-3 border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-3">🎮 Gameplay Tactics Using the Solver</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">Beyond finding words, here's how to use the solver strategically during your game:</p>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-blue-300 mt-6 mb-2">🪝 Hook Strategy</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">A "hook" is adding a single letter to an existing word on the board to form a new word. Use the solver to find hooks:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-4">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Set "Starts with" to the existing word's last letter + your tiles — find words that extend it</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Use "Ends with" set to the first letter of a word on the board — find words you can place in front</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>The S hook is the most powerful — adding S to almost any noun gives you two words scored simultaneously</span></li>
    </ul>

    <div class="rounded-lg border border-blue-800/40 bg-blue-900/10 p-4 mb-4">
      <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium mb-2">📘 Front Hooks vs Back Hooks</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-2"><strong class="text-white">Front Hook:</strong> A letter placed BEFORE an existing word to make a new word. Example: adding <span class="font-mono text-blue-400">S</span> before <span class="font-mono">COLD</span> makes <span class="font-mono text-green-400">SCOLD</span>. Or <span class="font-mono text-blue-400">T</span> before <span class="font-mono">RAIN</span> makes <span class="font-mono text-green-400">TRAIN</span>.</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-400 mb-2"><strong class="text-white">Back Hook:</strong> A letter placed AFTER an existing word. Example: adding <span class="font-mono text-blue-400">S</span> after <span class="font-mono">CAT</span> makes <span class="font-mono text-green-400">CATS</span>. Or <span class="font-mono text-blue-400">H</span> after <span class="font-mono">WIT</span> makes <span class="font-mono text-green-400">WITH</span>.</p>
      <p class="text-xs text-gray-400"><strong class="text-white">Why this matters:</strong> Front hooks are rarer and harder to spot — if you can front-hook a word on a premium square, opponents often don't see it coming. Back hooks (especially S, D, R, E) are more common but still score double since you get points for both the new letter AND the perpendicular word you're forming.</p>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-blue-300 mt-6 mb-2">🧮 Rack Balance Between Turns</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">Don't just play the highest-scoring word. Think about what you're leaving on your rack:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-4">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>After solving, look at 2–3 of the top results and check the Rack Leave panel for each</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Prefer leaves with a mix of vowels and consonants (3V/4C or 4V/3C)</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Keeping E, R, S, T, or a blank on your rack is almost always good — they combine with anything</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Avoid leaving duplicate letters (two I's, two O's) — they reduce your flexibility next turn</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-blue-300 mt-6 mb-2">🎯 Playing High-Value Tiles</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">Q, Z, X, J are worth 8–10 points each but can clog your rack. Tactics:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-4">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Use "Contains" filter with Q, Z, X, or J to see all words you can make right now — play them fast, don't hoard</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Memorize QI (Q without U) — it's often the only way to play Q without wasting a turn</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>ZA, ZO, XI, XU, JO — these 2-letter words let you dump rare tiles on premium squares for big points</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>If you can't play a high-value tile in 2 turns, consider exchanging — the points you lose from a blocked rack cost more</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-blue-300 mt-6 mb-2">🚀 Bingo Hunting (All 7 Tiles)</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">Playing all 7 tiles earns a +50 point bonus. Use the solver to hunt for bingos:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-4">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Enter all 7 tiles in the solver and look for 7-letter results — the Best Opening panel shows these with "bingo!" labels</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>If no 7-letter word exists, try removing one tile (play 6 letters + draw 6 next turn for better bingo chance)</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Learn the "SATINE" stem — tiles A, E, I, N, S, T form the most bingo combinations with any 7th letter</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>If you have 6 of the SATINE letters, hold them and play your odd letter — next draw often completes a bingo</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-blue-300 mt-6 mb-2">🛡️ Defensive Play</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">Sometimes the best move isn't the highest-scoring one — it's the one that blocks your opponent:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-4">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>After solving, check if your top word opens a Triple Word Score for your opponent — if so, pick the next-best word that doesn't</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Use the "Ends with" filter to find words that close off board lanes without opening premium squares</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>In the endgame, check the Tile Bag probability — if your opponent likely has Q/Z stuck, keep the board tight</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-blue-300 mt-6 mb-2">📈 Parallel Plays (Double Scoring)</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">Place a word alongside an existing word so each adjacent pair of letters forms a valid 2-letter word. You score for ALL new words formed:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-4">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Study the Two-Letter Words panel on the solver — these are your parallel play building blocks</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>A 4-letter parallel play can score 40+ points because you're forming 5 words simultaneously (your word + 4 two-letter cross-words)</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Use "Contains" to find words with specific letters that create valid parallels against what's on the board</span></li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-medium text-blue-300 mt-6 mb-2">⏱️ Endgame Tactics</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">When the tile bag is empty and you know your opponent's approximate tiles:</p>
    <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-4">
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Use the Tile Bag tracker — once it shows 0 in bag, you know exactly what your opponent holds</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>If you're ahead: play short, safe words that close the board. Don't give them openings.</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>If you're behind: look for spots where you can play long words on premium squares. Use the solver aggressively.</span></li>
      <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-blue-400 mt-0.5">→</span><span>Going out first gives you bonus points (your opponent's remaining tiles are added to your score)</span></li>
    </ul>

    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-6">🎯 Want to dive deeper into strategy? Read <a href="/blog/scrabble-tile-strategy-letters-scoring" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 underline underline-offset-2">Scrabble Tile Strategy: Letters, Scores & Smart Rack Management</a></p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white mt-10 mb-3 border-l-4 border-blue-500 pl-3">Data Management — Nuke, Download & Relink</h2>
    <div class="border border-purple-800/50 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6 bg-gray-900/50">
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">All your data (memory workbench, achievements, settings) lives in your browser's localStorage. Here's how to manage it:</p>
      
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mt-4 mb-2">📥 Download Your Data</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">Go to <a href="/settings" class="text-blue-400 hover:underline">Settings</a> and click <strong class="text-white">Download Backup</strong>. This exports all your memory workbench, scores, and achievements as a JSON file you can keep safe.</p>
      
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mt-4 mb-2">🔗 Relink on Another Device</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">Your anonymous User ID (UUID) is the key to your data. To access your memory workbench on another browser or device:</p>
      <ol class="space-y-1 text-gray-300 mb-3 list-decimal list-inside">
        <li>Copy your UUID from Settings on your current device</li>
        <li>On the new device, go to Settings → Restore</li>
        <li>Paste your UUID and click Restore — your words and achievements will sync</li>
      </ol>
      
      <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-white mt-4 mb-2">💣 Nuke localStorage</h3>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3">Need a fresh start? The <strong class="text-white">Nuke</strong> button in Settings permanently deletes ALL local data — memory workbench, achievements, preferences, and your User ID. This cannot be undone.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm">⚠️ Always download a backup before nuking. Once gone, there's no way to recover your data without the UUID.</p>
    </div>

    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-white mt-6 mb-2">🍪 Cookies & What Happens Without Them</h3>
    <div class="border border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6 bg-gray-900/50">
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-4">If you prefer not to be tracked, <strong class="text-white">reject all cookies</strong> via the 🍪 button (bottom-left corner) or disable cookies in your browser.</p>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3"><strong class="text-white">Features impacted without cookies:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300 mb-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">⚠️</span><span><strong class="text-white">Memory Workbench won't persist</strong> — your collection relies on localStorage linked to your session</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">⚠️</span><span><strong class="text-white">Achievements will reset</strong> — progress resets on each visit</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">⚠️</span><span><strong class="text-white">Theme/settings forgotten</strong> — dark mode and preferences reset</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-amber-400 mt-0.5">⚠️</span><span><strong class="text-white">Cookie banner reappears</strong> — shows on every page load</span></li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-gray-300 mb-3"><strong class="text-white">Features that still work fully:</strong></p>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-300">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-400 mt-0.5">✓</span><span>Word solver — works entirely client-side</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-400 mt-0.5">✓</span><span>Tile probability & rack leave analysis</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-400 mt-0.5">✓</span><span>Best opening moves calculator</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-400 mt-0.5">✓</span><span>Reference panels (two-letter words, Q without U, rare letters)</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-400 mt-0.5">✓</span><span>Blog content and guides</span></li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-4">The core word-finding functionality works perfectly without cookies. Only persistence and personalisation features are affected.</p>
    </div>

  </div>

